es.upm.gib.eutilsrdfwrapper.interfaceWeb
Class QuerySessions

java.lang.Object
  es.upm.gib.eutilsrdfwrapper.interfaceWeb.QuerySessions

public class QuerySessions
extends java.lang.Object

This class essentially offers the same querying functionality found on the QueryProcessor class. The public methods offered however always return instantly, returning a session identifier for following up the progress of the query, which remains executing on the background.

We can let the library generate the session identifier (in this case the code will make sure that this value is unique) or provide our own value of session identifier (in this case it is responsibility of the client to check that no other query shares this identifier)

The session identifier allows asking for the progress of the submitted query (or asking for the result, if it is complete). The result will be, as usual, the path to the generated results file (or an error message, if it starts with the "@@@" prefix)

processQuery

public static void processQuery(java.lang.String sessionID,
                                Results results,
                                java.util.List<java.lang.String> dbList)
Executes a SPARQL query against the arrayexpress database, using a specific experiment. A file containing the results in SPARQL Result format is generated.

The query is executed in background. A session identifier is generated and returned by this method. This identifier allows following up the progress of the query

Parameters:
sessionID - the session identifier to use for this query. This identifier should never match any previously used session identifier
